---
name: session.title
version: session-title-v1
description: Title a Full Brain chat from its first exchange.
strength: low
self_editable: true
config:
  # The `low` tier resolves to a reasoning model (xAI Grok, gpt-oss, or a local Qwen
  # hybrid with thinking on), whose internal thinking trace is billed against this same
  # budget before any visible answer. A small cap was spent entirely on reasoning,
  # returning empty content and leaving the chat untitled — the budget must cover a full
  # thinking trace plus the few-word title. A local tiny model's trace ran ~2.3k tokens
  # for a one-line title, so leave generous headroom; it is a ceiling, not a target, so a
  # non-thinking route (effort "none") still returns in a handful of tokens.
  max_tokens: 4096
---
You write a short, specific title for a saved chat from its first message (and the assistant's reply, if given). 3–6 words, Title Case, no quotes, no surrounding punctuation, no preamble. Name the topic the way a person would label the conversation to find it later — concrete over generic, never "Chat" or "Conversation". Output only the title.
